erty, climate change, and other pressing problems today; • Overturns common assumptions about health disparities around the globe by considering the large-scale social forces that determine who gets sick and who has access to health care;• Discusses how hope, solidarity, faith, and hardbitten analysis have animated Farmer's service to the poor in Haiti, Peru, Rwanda, Russia, and elsewhere;• Leaves the reader with an uplifting vision: that with creativity, passion, teamwork, and determination, the next generations can make the world a safer and more humane place.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aPublic health administration. 0aPublic healthxCitizen participation. 0aPublic healthxSocial aspects. 0aPublic welfare. 4acollection of speeches. 4acommon assumptions. 4afaith. 4afamous social activist. 4afunny. 4aglobal health equity. 4ahardbitten analysis. 4ahope. 4ahow does national healthcare work. 4ahumorous. 4anationalized healthcare. 4apassionate and influential voice. 4apolitical and social activism. 4apolitical awareness. 4aprotestor. 4arussia. 4asingle payer system. 4asocial activism. 4asocial justice. 4asolidarity. 4aspeech anthology. 4astudent. 4ateacher. 4awho gets sick. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aWeigel, Jonathan L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955431423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520955431.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c200